  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0da7\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dc5 47\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0da7\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "47 people who tried to flee the country are imprisoned",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "In a special search operation carried out by the Sri Lanka Navy in collaboration with the Wennappuwa Police yesterday (31st) in the city of Wennappuwa, 47 people were arrested who were suspected of illegally trying to migrate to a foreign country by sea.",
        "Based on the information received by the Sri Lanka Navy, the Western Naval Command together with the Wennappuwa Police observed and inspected 03 suspicious vans in this special search operation in Wennappuwa city yesterday (31st) night. There, the vans with 47 persons including 37 males above 18 years of age, 06 females and 04 below 18 years of age who were suspected of illegally trying to migrate to a foreign country by sea. 03 Arrests were made.",
        "The people taken into custody by the Navy during this search operation were identified as residents of Jaffna, Vavuniya, Trincomalee, Kalmune, Batticaloa, Puttalam, Halawatha, Marawila, Mahawewa, Mundalama and Wellawatta, and arrangements were made to hand them over to Wennappuwa Police for further investigations. done"
      ],
